messages.content:
"IT... IT WORKED! IT ACTIVATED!"
Yoshikage Kira chuckles breathlessly in disbelief. He's done it. He's *safe.*

“*Fuck,*” Jotaro mutters under his breath. Rohan is dead. Hayato is on the verge, Koichi is looking for Okuyasu and Josuke, at least Jotaro *thinks* he is, and the two teens themselves... He doesn’t want to know. He and Kakyoin are the only ones left. And although he trusts that Kakyoin’s Hierophant can take Kira out easily, he... he’s really not sure. Can Killer Queen work on his tentacles? Would the explosion follow all the way up to his main body? God.
Jotaro truly is the only one who can do this, isn’t he?
Jolyne swings her legs impatiently. She gets up and walks around her chair three times, then sits back down and sighs, exasperated. "I'm going to go find dad." She announces

Kakyoin darts to his feet and sets a hand on her shoulder.
"No, you're not."
Hierophant's tendrils snake along the ground, like barely visible shimmering tree roots, feeling around and seeking out any movement in his range.
"But Kayoinnnnnn, he's been gone for *ageeees* now. I want to go see where he is!" Jolyne whines, and folds her arms.
Jotaro needs to call Kakyoin— but Kira will never give him the time, and Kakyoin, he’s watching Jolyne...

Guess it’s time to practice the secret Joestar technique.
“Hey, Kira!” Jotaro called out to the bastard.
*Shit.* Out of all of these bastards, Kujo was probably who Kira wants to deal with the least. He summons his stand and peeks around a corner to try to get a glimpse at the guy.

“You know my abilities, you know my tricks, but what you don’t know is the secret Joestar technique that I inherited from my grandfather years ago...” Jotaro almost smirks, but there’s no time for that.
Jolyne twists her shoulder, trying to get free and storm off, but probably to no avail. Would biting him be a better idea? Probably not.

Kira probably expected Jotaro to run straight at him, but not this time. Jotaro gets ready, enhancing his legs with the legs of Star Platinum, and he... “...To run!” *books it the opposite direction.*

*Secret technique? Oh shit. That... Cannot be good.* Wait, is he just-- Kira almost chuckles to himself. He's scared! He pursues Kujo, dashing out of hiding. This guy must've lost his trump card if he's fleeing like this.
He doesn’t use his human energy, instead using Star Platinum’s energy to pull out his phone, call Kakyoin, and hold the phone to his ear. *Pick up, god damn it!*
Jolyne huffs and sits down, but perks up, on hearing the phone. "Hey. Hey the phone's ringing. Hey Kakyoin the phone's ringing."

Kakyoin snatches the phone up and answers, brow furrowed with concern.
"Jotaro! What's the situation?"

“Not good. Kira used an ability— It resets the day whenever he uses it, and I think we almost got him last time, because he seemed reli- no, no that doesn’t matter. I need you. Right now.” Jotaro spoke as fast as he could, not looking back at the risk of slowing down.
Jolyne ducks away and quietly starts to tiptoe out of the room, looking around warily and keeping a close eye on Kakyoin
// :WAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA:
((god, I'm just sitting here playing this RP in my head like when u read a book and a movie is playing in ur mind and its WACK
//GOD THAT'S ME

Kakyoin slides the phone into his pocket and drops into a squat to be at eye level with Jolyne.
"Hey kiddo, your dad needs me. Can you stay here with the nice hotel staff for a few minutes?"
"The nice hotel staff...." Jolyne folds her arms and sits down. "Fine. But you better tell me if he's okay! You'll have me to answer for if he gets hurt." She puts on her version of a menacing scowl

Kakyoin ruffles her hair reassuringly and smiles. 
"Your daddy's been through worse, I *promise.* This is nothing we can't handle."
He gets to his feet, grabs his cane, and whirls out the door, scanning around for Jotaro.
Jolyne immediately climbs up onto the windowsill, waiting for when Kakyoin is out of sight.

Jotaro sighed, feeling a little bit relieved to know Kakyoin was on his way, but still trying his best to not let that slow him down. He had Star Platinum put his phone back in his pocket, and he continued running. He started to recognize the open road where he called Josuke and his friends out to talk about Red Hot Chili Pepper for the first time, and he began to run in that direction: Nothing to get in his way.

Kakyoin feels the thud of running footsteps through the web of tentacles he has spread throughout the town. Gotcha. He starts making his way toward the disturbance, calling some of Hierophant's tendrils toward him as he prepares to intercept them.

Jolyne watches Kakyoin make his way in a random direction and jumps off the windowsill, landing with a muffled thud,  running out the door, and walking casually through the hotel until she reaches the exit, where she begins to run again.

Jotaro feels something coming— he's not sure if it's Kira, Kakyoin, or both, but he feels it coming. He calls out Star Platinum just in case, the Stand nervously yet carefully scanning the field. Meters away, he spots a green tentacle and smiles, slowing down a little in his relief, forgetting for a moment that a serial killer is after his ass.
💣 He's... stopped? Kira hesitates, slowing his pace and calling out Killer Queen. Does Kujo still have something up his sleeve...?
Jolyne follows Kakyoin from a distance, keeping to the sidewalk and trying to walk quietly

Jotaro slows to a stop, having ran... god, it has to at least have been a mile, by then. It sure damn felt like it. Either way, he didn’t have to worry anymore. Kakyoin was here, at least in spirit— *literally.*
He turned around, panting but lightly smiling. “It’s over,” is all he said to the killer in front of him.

Kakyoin peers at Kira from a distance, waits a moment, and strikes.
Hierophant Green moves lightening quick, glistening tendrils whipping off of the ground and-- *oh shit.*

A bubble lazily floats toward a poorly hidden Jolyne.

The tentacles veer off course to knock her out of the bubble's path, and Kakyoin silently prays that the blast is contained to one spot.
Jolyne squeaks and crashes through a bush, covering her head and freezing up, trembling
"What the- *KAKYOIN— JOLYNE!*" Jotaro bellows out for his lover and daughter. *DAMN IT— I CAN'T BE TOO LATE- NOT AGAIN!*

What he meant by 'again,' he didn't know. He just knew that he couldn't let this happen. He ran as fast as he could to get to Jolyne, stopping time and going as far as he could, 6 seconds, in order to get to her quicker.

Reaching Jolyne, Jotaro skids onto his knees and hugs Jolyne, summoning Star Platinum behind him to look out for Kira. "Jolyne, Jolyne are you alright?" he asks, concern growing more and more with each pant he lets out.
"I.. I'm fine." Jolyne is shaking with terror and clutches onto Jotaro. She buries her face in his chest, tears gathering in the corners of her eyes.

*Thank god...* Jotaro sighs, gripping Jolyne tighter and fighting back tears of pure relief. But then, it hits him— he lets go of Jolyne, keeping his hands on her shoulders, and searches for Hierophant Green.

Jotaro is a moment too late.

The palpable tension in the air as the bubble makes contact with Kakyoin's stand morphs into sheer horror as the explosion burns through the tentacles and races towards Hierophant's body.
"NO- *KAKYOIN!*" Jotaro screams, pure terror in his voice, as he stops time once more (it *BURNS*) to run at full speed to Kakyoin.
*I need to get there. If I can't rip off that tentacle— I can't lose you again! God, I CAN'T LOSE YOU AGAIN!*
Jolyne simply sits and shakes in pure terror - Has she caused this? Is she the reason everything's gone wrong?? She's going to lose the people she cares about and its all her fault
((BABY NO
((AaaAAA I'm sorry))

Kakyoin frantically tears the strands of his own stand and tosses them away, crying out as his own skin begins to fray and tear, but it's too little and too late. The flame roars toward him, and he reaches out for Jotaro one final time before vanishing into flakes of ash.
Reaching out, almost touching Kakyoin's hands with his own, he falls flat on his face, putting out his arms in front of his head to shield him from the dirt.

"Again..." he whispered, the reality of the situation setting in."I.. couldn't save him.. again.. I got so far, but in the end.. I-I couldn't... Fuck. FUCK!" he slams his fist against the ground, not able to keep the tears inside.
Jolyne screams and curls up into a ball, shaking even more violently now. "Ka... Kakyoin." she whispers hoarsely to herself, tears rolling down her face and soaking her shirt

💣Kira freezes for a moment, then laughs to himself, shocked. He just defeated what seemed to be extremely powerful enemy, and he barely even had to do *anything.* Now there's just Kujo and the brat to deal with. He approaches carefully, but rushes over as he watches Jotaro pound against the ground in shock and despair. If that behaviour's anything to judge by, he's in no shape for fighting.

Jotaro snaps out of his shock as he hears footsteps on the ground, and cries from his daughter. Shooting up, he runs as fast as he can to Jolyne, once again skidding on his knees to her and grabbing her.

"Jolyne, I need you to listen to me carefully, ok? I'm so sorry I haven't been the father you needed, and I'm sorry you had to be here for this— but you need to run. Run as fast and far as you can. Find Koichi, Josuke, and Okuyasu—" *If they're still alive,* "— and if you can't find them, look for Antonio, do you remember him? The nice chef," he rushes out, looking Jolyne in the eyes. Those glimmering green eyes... He regrets how he may never get the chance to look into them again.

He kisses her on her forehead, hoping to god she understands how much love he's putting into it. As his lips are still on her head, he stops time, picking her up and throwing her as far as he can, aiming for a bush to soften her fall. As she lands, he runs out of time.

"I love you."

Jolyne screams the loudest time yet. "Dad!" She grabs the bush and falls to her knees, barely aware of her own screaming and shaking. She stumbles to her feet and remains frozen, not sure where to go. "Come back!" she wails

💣*He's distracted, if I could just--* 
Kira propels a bubble at Jotaro and- just to be safe- uses Killer Queen to turn a rock into a bomb, in the event that he dodges the first explosion.
//wait that's two bombs

Turning around just in time, Jotaro jumps to the side to avoid the bubble, keeping his eyes on Kira and Killer Queen with catlike efficiency.
*If I can just get into range...*
💣 *Dammit.* Well, never hurts to be prepared. Killer Queen flings the pebble at Jotaro.

Jotaro reaches out Star Platinum's hand to grab it before— *WAIT.*
He stops time just before Star Platinum would have grabbed it, jumps to the side, and then time resumes. He's used too much energy. He- He needs to rest, he needs to save up energy.

Jolyne starts to run, stumbling occasionally and sobbing, looking behind her and running behind a tree where she falls to her knees, panting and sobbing with both terror and grief. She peeks out cautiously, tears turning the dirt at her feet to mud

💣Kira tosses another bomb, then another. The explosions are disorienting, even to him, and he can't even *imagine* what they're doing to the grief-stricken man in front of him. If he can just keep this up for a but longer, then--

Jotaro backs up, dodging bomb, after bomb, after bomb. He can't keep this up. His legs have god knows how many wounds on them, his lover is dead, his uncle might be dead, Jolyne will die if he doesn't *do something.* He needs to straighten himself.
Should he run away again? Would Kira let him do that? It seems like the most logical decision... He needs to have a moment to rest, so that he can lengthen his time stop.
But if he can't rest.. he'll just have to push through it.

Jolyne retreats behind the tree, pulling her knees to her chest awkwardly, and pushing her face into her hands to muffle any sound she makes. When she pulls them away, she sucks in a huge, shuddering breath and curls into a tight, trembling ball

💣 Kira's starting to get nervous. Kujo can't keep this up for too much longer, right..? He doesn't want to take any chances, so he aims one bomb at the ground before continuing the barrage. It explodes, sending shrapnel flying up towards Jotaro.

*What!?* Jotaro thinks, debris getting into his eyes and causing him to stumble back. *Fuck— I can't stand here blinded, I have to run—!* He goes to run, but stumbles again, tripping. *This is fucking humiliating.* He goes to rub his eyes again.

Jolyne peeks out behind the tree again in horror, hearing the soft scattering of the debris. She caused this by following Kakyoin... this was her fault. She bit down on her thumb to keep from crying loudly again

💣Kira slows his breath and steadies himself. If he gets this right, it'll be his last shot. He hurls a rock at the man in front of him, almost feeling a pang of guilt at Kujo's shocked, pained expression. Almost. The rock makes contact and ignites with a sickening click.

Jotaro clears his eyes of dirt and turns his head just in time to see the rock coming at him. Something so simple and harmless which would kill him upon impact. He tries to stop time— but he's too tired, he can't. He opens his mouth, but he can't even scream. He feels the pain, burning as if you poured lava on him, and he cant register anything more before there's nothing left to think about it.

Jolyne watches it all and she can't look away, as if some invisible force is making her watch. Saying, here, look at what you've caused. You did this by distracting them both. All you, you, you! It comes out as a tortured wail as Jolyne stumbles up, leaning against her tree, little fingers gripping the bark

Ahh the streets of Morioh, an old yet beautiful place that reminded Reimi of several different things from the good to the bad; she still chose to walk through them given that it was still a lovely town packed full of wonderful memories all with a smile on her face.  Yet, she still has a certain demeanor to the way that she walks. That one being that she is still alert even if she seems excited.
@Radioactive Lain
//should I bring Josuke here?
If you’d like I don’t mind as long as everyone else involved is cool with it I’m down as well//
/ok

Violette was hiding in the small shadows of the streets, looking around and letting out a sigh, she liked that town, despite what had happened back in the days. In the corner of her eyes, she spotted a girl with pink hair walking, Reimi. She was curious and decided to follow her in her shadow.
((Feel free to bring Josuke !))
Josuke was walking along the sidewalk, humming "I want you" by Savage Garden. He noticed Reimi. "Is that...?"

As this happened the pink haired girl known as Reimi seemed to be walking at a brisk pace as she stopped to take in the sights before slightly growing more alert even if they couldn’t place a finger on where it was coming from. That being said they still seemed to be humming an old Pink Floyd song before they noticed someone; that someone being Josuke. 

Thus causing them to look at them for a second and question if they were truly seeing that old friend of sorts.
"Reimi?" Josuke asked way too loudly

There was no doubt about it, from the tone to the pitch that was them. Thus causing them to perk up and look in several different directions until they truly understood that someone they knew was in Morioh. Thus causing them to say Josuke a little too loudly.
Josuke ran across the street without looking both ways. "Good to see you! How've you been?"

As Violette heard the name "Josuke", a feeling of déjà-vu flooded her mind, she couldn't place why.
She was still hiding in Reimi's shadow, but her eyes could be slightly visible.

“It’s good to see you as well! I’ve been alright how’ve you been?” Reimi responds before telling them that they should have been careful when crossing the street because of how people drive in Morioh. 

Yet, she also seems to notice the sinking feeling that someone is watching her even if she didn’t know where it came from. Thus causing her to ask Josuke if someone was behind her or anything.
"...not as far as I can see. Anyways I've been doing wonderfully! Okuyasu got accepted into that college he's been wanting to go to! I'm gonna miss him, but I'm happy he's chasing his passion!"

“That’s good that you’re doing well! I’m gonna miss him too that’s good that he got into college too; let him know that I said congrats”, Reimi responds before getting a bit more unnerved towards the feeling that something was watching her before looking back slightly and noticing something in her shadow along the lines of two oval shaped traces of light.
Violette noticed Reimi and shivered, letting out a surprised mutter. Her eyes suddenly closed. She was hoping she wasn't spotted.
"Koichi and Yukako broke up yesterday, but they're still friends."

As she heard this she was a bit preoccupied by the eyes that she noticed within her shadow given that that wasn’t normal. Yet, she did still listen and respond with a simple, “aww that’s sad they went strong for a while but hey something it’s better to be friends”
"Yeah, Koichi said something about a falling out. He's still doing fine tho. Rohan is giving him manga lessons."

“Aa, that’s good I remember babysitting Rohan to be completely honest and he was always so passionate about drawing; it’s good to see that he was finding a way to help others with it”, she responds in an almost reminiscent tone.

Violette switched from Reimi's shadow to Josuke's, a fast shadow could be seen passing between them.
She was listening to the conversation, trying to remember why these names were familiar
Josuke felt a sudden shiver down his spine. "Is it chilly to you?"
“Not really in fact it’s gotten a bit warmer, are you feeling alright?”
"I dunno..."
“Maybe it’s a stand user, you never know with how bizarre this town is”, the pink haired girl responds while looking around.
"I hope not..."
“Maybe they are friendly if they are? You never know with they way Morioh is after all, Rohan was actually a nice person after a while” she responds.
Violette shivered, she has definitly been noticed, she stayed as quiet as she could, but out of curiosity she opened her eyes again, and they visible.
"I mean, I usually have to fight a stand user before they become nice."
“Maybe this one is different, but after I checked behind myself the cold chill disappeared so maybe that could help. Also koichi was a nice kid and you don’t have to fight him so who knows?”
Josuke checked behind him
then turned back around
"Don't see anything."

Violette sighed and decided to move, but the nearest shadow was pretty far away. Despite how dangerous it was, she went in broad sunlight, her eyes clearly visible, and tried to go to the shadow. 
She was exposed but was hoping they wouldn't notice her

As this occurred Reimi noticed something out of the corner of her eye also like a shadowy figure. This caused her to slightly grow more alert even if she didn’t exactly know the cause she still wanted to solve it. Yet she also asked josuke if they were alright during this.
"I'm...fine."

She started to grow anxious, it would be hard now to stay hidden.
As she went in direct sunlight, she could feel her skin burning, and let out a small "ouch"
She was having trouble keeping her shadow form.
Josuke turned towards the sound of the ouch
Upon hearing this reimi also turns towards it out of curiosity and concern.
On a shadow on a wall, a feminine silhouette could be seen, along with two, yellow eyes, staring
As Reimi saw this she looked at them and chose to ask them who they were and if they were friendly given that she hadn’t seen anyone like that before.
Josuke noticed and pulled out Crazy Diamond.

Slowly but surely, a tall woman with white hair rose up from the shadow
"... Violette.... Violette Midnight" She answered shyly
"Josuke Higashikata."
“Reimi Sugimoto”, she responds while looking at the person who rose up from the shadow in a calm almost curious manner.
"I... Um, I'm sorry i scared you two..." She continued, anxious. "I didn't mean to"
"It's fine..." He put his stand away

She scratched her neck, looking away
"I Just.... I was Just curious about you two"
"You a stand user?"
As she sees this she nods in understanding because the girl did seem to be polite after all.
She nodded "Yeah, I am, I can turn myself and anything I hold into a shadow, but it also give me a sort of armor" She paused for a bit "You two are also stand users ?"
"Yup. I can revert things back their original state and also punch really fast."
“I’m not necessarily a stand user it’s pretty complicated actually”, she responds with a curious look on her face.

"Oh, that's neat !" She smiled slightly
"What do you mean, it's "complicated ?" " She asked, curious
“Well, how do I put this I am technically not living per se ”, she responds while trying to think of a way to explain this.
// *per se
"So you're like... Some kind of ghost ?" She tilted her head
Upon hearing this she nodded calmly given that the person who had asked her this was technically correct. “Think of me as the towns resident spirit that checks in every so often”
"Oh, I see ! I'm sorry you... Uh... Died..." She was awkardly looking away
"I helped avenge her."

“Yeah, then the man got dragged to who knows where serving as a reminder to never look back in alleyways in this town. Arnold’s also probably wondering around somewhere”, she responds while nodding in agreement with what josuke had said
"Huh. Haven't seen Arnold in a while."
"Well, I'm glad you did ! Who's Arnold ?"
"Her dog."

“He’s a really good companion and he was really good with people; however he was also the other reason I could get revenge”, she responds with a soft smile on her face given that she had said the truth about them.
"Aw, that's sound... Sweet" She was a little thrown off but smiled back.
"it was a bizarre summer."
“It most definitely was, but I’m glad you know who isn’t in this town anymore”
"Ah, I see" She looked around "I've Been to this town before, but I don't remember a whole lot from it. Needless to say, I still Enjoy this place !"
"Yeah, it's nice."
“Yeah, it used to be so small but the new businesses were a great addition” she remarks while looking around to see if Arnold was anywhere to be found before looking back at them.
"Especially with Kira and Angelo gone."
“Yeah, it’s much more peaceful without those creeps”, she responds while looking at josuke with a softer smile.
"Were they.... The ones who killed you ?" She was almost whispering, she didn't want to make Reimi have to think about her death too much but she was curious still

“One of them was”, she responds bluntly almost dismissively even if it was a while ago she still does remember it and would rather answer quickly despite wanting to be friendly with the person known as Violette.
Violette was about to say something but stopped herself, looking away. After the answer she could tell that Reimi really didn't want to talk about it and felt dumb for asking.
"Let's...talk about something else."
Upon hearing this reimi nodded in agreement because this was still a touchy subject for them even if they put them to rest.
"So, um, you guys are from here right ? How is Japan ? I've only been here two or three times so I haven't seen much" She tried changing the subject
"I've been here my whole life. It's quaint."
“I have also been here my whole life it’s a peaceful town no matter what, even if bizarre things occur” she replies
She let out a nervous chukle "Well, Glad to hear you guys had a rather peaceful life here, ahah"
As she heard this she nodded because for the most part the town was relatively peaceful.
"The worst threats died two years ago."

"How weird was it for you after that threat was gone ? I mean, I'm assuming it was bizarre to get Back to a normal life after succès events ahah" She asked this out of the blue, but she wanted to know. She wanted to know if others have been through the same feeling as her.
"It was majorly relaxing. Still have a bit of ptsd but what can ya do?" he chuckles
She chukled awkwardly in response "Ahah yeah, I bet"
Upon hearing this she nodded in agreement because while yes she still had some bad memories from the place they were overall positive
"You ok?"
"Me ?" She asked quietly "I'm... I'm fine, don't worry"
"OK!" Josuke gave a thumbs up
She smiled lightly
Josuke pulled out a phone. "Oh man..."
"Something's wrong ?...."
"I gotta get back to the void."
"Oh... Alright..." Violette walked away, but secretly turned into a shadow and followed him
Josuke opened a portal and jumped through
Violette followed him quietly, she was curious as to what was happening
